Comment: This annotation is mainly because a puzzling position in the end. My opponent resigned. I tried to create a puzzle from this position, but it halted as "too many possible variations". It was a nice mate in 13 moves that for a moment I thought it would really "work". And maybe it does... but I'll need a program to check it for sure. GK's puzzle engine is a good tool to check a position, but it stops too quickly for some complex positions.
